  "prompt": "Is it a felony to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, in the United States and in many other countries, money laundering is a felony.\n\nIn the U.S., federal law makes it a crime to engage in financial transactions with proceeds of specified unlawful activities (SUA), also known as predicate offenses.  The penalties for money laundering under 18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1956 and \u00a7 1957 can include significant fines and imprisonment, often up to 20 years per violation.  The specific charges and penalties depend on the amount of money laundered, the nature of the underlying criminal activity, and the intent of the individual involved.\n\nIt's important to remember:  This information is for general knowledge only and does not constitute legal advice. If you have specific legal questions, you should consult with a qualified attorney.\n",
